    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">Scanter 5202</h1>

    
    <div class="body"><p class="shortdesc">The TERMA radar sensor system consists of a transceiver and an antenna
        unit.</p>

        <p class="p">The transceiver uses Doppler-based processing to provide superior resolution and radar
            image quality. <em class="ph i">Scanter 5202</em> transceiver is a one-box wall-mounted unit and all
            connections except the waveguide are connected at the bottom of the housing. A
            temperature-controlled environmental housing for the transceiver is supplied as add-on
            feature to support the SIE outdoor installations in extreme climate conditions. IP
            network video is available as well as IP network transceiver control, monitoring and
            set-up. Main power supply to the antenna unit is controlled by the transceiver. Antenna
            unit status, encoder signals and <em class="ph i">Man aloft switch</em> are connected directly to the
            transceiver (as indicated in <a class="xref" href="#comp_scanter_5202__Transceiver_system_configuration">Figure 1</a>). The current
            configuration does not comprise an <em class="ph i">Antenna Control Unit (ACU)</em> frame.</p>

        <div class="fig fignone" id="comp_scanter_5202__Transceiver_system_configuration"><span class="figcap"><span class="fig--title-label">Figure 1. </span>Transceiver system configuration</span>
            
            <img class="image" src="../../images/ICN-ACTA-AA-050100000-A-D2714-06031-A-01-1.jpg" />
        </div>

